  "body": "Phase F-edit wave 1 + wave 2 + the create-org-via-AI-Agent bootstrap shipped today across builds 33-37. Five new patch-shaped MCP tools (update_position, update_org_metadata, bump_version, add_position, delete_position, update_relationship, claim_org_create) with REST mirrors and audit log; the panel is read-only by design, all editing flows through MCP from the user's AI client. End-to-end true-bootstrap demonstrated: Director created a fresh openbraid account (yesteryacht@gmail.com), clicked the new 'Create Organization via AI Agent' button, pasted the prompt into a fresh AI conversation, walked through PIN ceremony, and landed a new four-position org (YesterYacht) with mission/vision/scope/governance/values/red_lines fully populated — zero JSON pasting, zero panel-side editing UI. Substrate + AI-in-client + MCP-as-seam holds. Three remaining Phase F items have been reframed by the work shipped today; F-chart-2 part 2 (github resolver + Refresh-from-master) and Phase G (self-host docs) are the obvious next runway. body_ref has per-build disposition, lessons learned, three follow-ups worth your judgment, and process notes from the day's near-misses.",
